Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

Cambodia has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Cambodia, see Return to the UK
Entry and borders
There are restrictions on travellers coming from, and nationals of, France, Germany, Italy, Spain, the USA and Iran.
If you wish to enter Cambodia you will need to:
get a visa prior to arrival —visa exemption policy and issuances of visa on arrival and e-visa are suspended indefinitely;
have a medical certificate, no longer than 72 hours prior to the date of travel, from a competent health authority stating you do not have COVID-19 ;
have a financial statement indicating that you have at least $50,000 for medical coverage;
spend 14-days in mandatory quarantine at a government designated care centre will be imposed upon arrival in Cambodia.
If you’re visiting or living in Cambodia and intend to leave, you should do so as soon as possible. The only current flight option out of Cambodia to the UK is via Seoul.
The Cambodia-Laos, Cambodia-Thailand and Cambodia-Vietnam land borders are closed.
Visas
Suspension of tourist visas, e-visas, visa on arrival and visa exemptions came in to effect on 31 March.
The latest information on visas from the relevant authorities is as below:
Tourist Visa: For all short term visitors arriving on or after 01 January 2020, tourist visas will be automatically extended and any overstay fines will be waived. Visitors are not required to go to the immigration department office for any kind of exit visa/stamp before departing. All departing visitors can proceed directly to the airport to depart through the normal immigration channels.
Other Visas: For non-tourist visas such as EG visas, there is no automatic extension in place and these can be renewed at any time in the usual way.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
